overview: The user wanted to add database functionality and an admin dashboard
  to their existing sleep questionnaire application, based on a provided
  Statement of Work. I evaluated the codebase, clarified specific requirements
  for demographic data and authentication complexity, and then proceeded with
  the implementation. This involved updating the application's data models to
  include new demographic fields, creating a  model in
  Prisma for PostgreSQL (NeonDB) database storage, and developing API endpoints
  for saving and retrieving questionnaire data, including a CSV export feature.
  A simple password-based authentication system was implemented for the admin
  dashboard. Initially, a custom session management approach was used, but this
  was later simplified to leverage Next.js middleware for more efficient route
  protection. The implementation included creating login and dashboard pages for
  administrators to view and download responses. The entire system was tested to
  confirm that questionnaire submissions were saved to the database, admin login
  worked correctly, and CSV data export was functional.
